{
  "stem": "20083.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 23.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But we were very friendly, and I even-- we even exchanged letters which, like everything else, unfortunately, most of it was destroyed during the blitz.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then in 1943, all of a sudden, I heard the-- saw the terrible news that he had been shot down by a Messerschmitt over the Gulf of Biscay and after he came back from a film festival in Lisbon.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As far as my schooling was concerned, I went to school in Dorset in Bryanston College until I think it was June or July of 1940.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "By that time, France had fallen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Belgium had fallen.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Holland.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And of course, Norway and Denmark.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they realized that England would be next.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And of course, that was Hitler's dream to conquer England.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he started bombing London to soften up the progress for his troops to invade England.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I had to leave Dorset because it was part of the coast, the southern coast.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the British were very much afraid of fifth columnists since quite a number of fifth columnists had helped the Nazis in France and Holland and Belgium.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they thought maybe we, too, were fifth columnists, forgetting that we were Jewish and forgetting that we were young at the time because there was another boy there my age too-- Lowenthal.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we had to leave Dorset in July of 1940.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They called-- they called us enemy aliens.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We even had to wear-- to carry a-- a little document with us at all times, which actually called us enemy aliens.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My picture was-- which, of course, I don't have anymore.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was back in 1939 or 1940 that we got it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that's in case anybody questions us, we could-- we always had to produce this picture.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
